Fale com $npcName:11000867[gender:0]$, no centro do $map:02000138$. Se alguém viu para onde foi seu amigo loiro, foi ele.
Vou arranjar um jeito de recompensar você por isso. Agradeço mais uma vez!
Humm. Algo me diz que você não veio comprar frutas.
Passou por aqui um homem loiro?
Sim, eu vi alguém assim. Aliás, ele causou uma impressão e tanto.
Mas acho que não lembro para onde ele foi…
Eu realmente gostaria de poder ajudar, $male:senhor,female:senhora$, mas não consigo me lembrar de nada com esses baderneiros perambulando por aí…
Vou dar um jeito neles se isso for refrescar sua memória.
Bem, já que falou nisso, pode ser que funcione. Você cuida do meu probleminha, e com certeza a minha memória vai voltar num instante.
Como é que alguém pode se concentrar com toda esta balbúrdia?
Mas que droga de memória fraca eu tenho… Heh heh…
Que coincidência! Minha memória está voltando agorinha mesmo. Pois então, esse sujeito loiro que você procura…
Eu o vi se esconder no $map:52000126$. Me parecia que ele estava passando por uns perrengues. Pelo jeito dele, o homem já não comia há um tempo…
Tem certeza de que não está $male:interessado,female:interessada$ em umas frutas frescas para a viagem? Isentas de insetos, garantido em 70% das vezes!
Eu não sei de porcaria nenhuma!
Faça o favor de me deixar em paz!
Calma. Estou procurando por um homem loiro. Alto, bonito…
Não tenho ideia de quem você está falando. Agora vá embora!
Por que você não me deixa em paz…?
N-não é da sua conta! Dá o fora daqui. Me deixe em paz!
$npcName:11003206[gender:0]$ e eu encontramos o cara loiro que você está procurando. Achei que essa seria a melhor forma de recompensar você por ter salvado meu irmão.
Ele está na $map:52000046$. Não é longe daqui. É melhor você se apressar antes que ele consiga escapulir de novo!
Então, você acha que eu matei o capitão…
Não posso me entregar à Vento das Trevas enquanto eu não limpar meu nome. Eu não matei Winn Stilton.
Talvez não, mas você ainda terá que vir comigo.
Então… Você não acredita em mim…
Lamento, mas não vou a lugar algum com você.
Essa foi por pouco, $MyPCName$. Se não fosse por $npcName:11003210[gender:0]$, eu nunca teria encontrado você.
O que aconteceu? Onde está o $npcName:11003215[gender:0]$?
Você estava sozinho quando te encontrei. Acho que $npcName:11003215[gender:0]$ já tinha fugido faz tempo…
Acho que é melhor avisar $npcName:11000044[gender:0]$ do que aconteceu…
Quando achei que tivéssemos perdido você, eu… Nunca senti isso antes, $MyPCName$. Você tem que tomar mais cuidado. Não sei o que eu faria se não pudesse mais ver você!
Você é $male:meu herói,female:minha heroína$! A verdade é que… eu admiro você!
Então, $npcName:11003215[gender:0]$ escapou. Acho que não tinha o que fazer mesmo…
Ainda não acabou. Vamos descer e decidir nossos próximos passos.
Eu devia ter mandado mais homens pra integrar a busca. Cada segundo que nós desperdiçamos é mais um segundo que a vida da $npcName:11000069[gender:1]$ está em perigo…
Primeiro, temos que… Espere aí. O que é essa algazarra?
Sem você, a $map:02000100$ podia ter acabado hoje. Obrigado.
Só estou cumprindo meu dever, Senhor.
Me poupe da modéstia. Você fez um bom trabalho lá. Infelizmente, vou estar ocupado demais limpando a $map:02000100$ para ajudar a procurar $npcName:11003215[gender:0]$ por enquanto…
Você e seu amigo devem retornar à $map:02000001$. Avise-os sobre o que aconteceu aqui… e o que aconteceu a Winn Stilton.
Me desculpe por não poder fazer mais nada para ajudar.
Vai ser bom dormir na minha própria cama de novo. $male:Pronto,female:Pronta$ pra voltar a $map:02000001$?
Não sei se tenho jeito pro trabalho de campo! Achei que ser da guarda era mais uma coisa de ficar parado e… você sabe… fazer a guarda…
Primeiro Winn Stilton, depois a $map:02000100$… choque após choque.
Isto é um assunto muito sério. A imperatriz deveria ouvir isso de você.
Sei que você tem uma história e tanto para me contar.
Acabamos de saber de $map:02000076$. Eles estão sendo atacados por criaturas das trevas. É a $map:02000100$, tudo de novo!

$MyPCName$, while you were helping us and Humanitas in carrying out missions, the remaining forces were sent to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>. After much effort, the scouts can finally explore beyond <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>.
You must be curious of that unknown place, right?
Good. I'll give you the details after we go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>. Then I'll see you in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>.
Hm? Why are you still here? Weren't you going to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>?
(Say that you didn't know everyone was here.)
We set up a temporary base to efficiently explore beyond the foothold. We have already finished our initial exploration.
It was a successful exploration. We discovered <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020066$</font> is beyond this place.
Refugees that were expelled by Tairen live there, but we don't know the exact situation yet. We wanted to get close, but had to pull back because there were too many from Kharon.

The situation isn't good. We have a mountain of things to check such as where and what <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is doing, the size of the Daemon Army stationed here, and if there are any other forces. We are in need of an optimal scout.
Who do you think? It's us, <font color="#ffd200">Strike Team $npcName:11004578[gender:0]$</font>!
This is not just the opinion of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004578[gender:0]$</font>. I, even <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font>, believe that you are the one.
There is no scout as skilled as you and traveled all of Kritias. We would like you to take this on. Is it too much to ask?
$MyPCName$, we'll be at ease if you're going.

We confirmed the <font color="#ffd200">Refugee Shelter</font> is beyond the foothold, but we failed to enter due to the large number of the Kharon. I want to know whether the refugees expelled by Tairen are doing well. Could you check this out first?
And... if possible, it would be great if you could let the refugees know that Humanitas would like to help.
(Say that you understand and will also decrease the number of the Kharon.)
Thank you so much. I believe in you.
Defeat the Kharon obstructing your entry to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020066$</font>, and check whether the refugees are doing well.
Who are you? How did you come here?
(Say that you went beyond the foothold and defeated the Kharon to come.)
(Say yes and ask where this place is.)
What great abilities! Oh, look at me. Did you ask where this place is? This place is a settlement by refugees expelled by Tairen who are avoiding the Kharon.
You don't look like an exile like me. What is your identity?
(Say that you are from <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font> and helping Humanitas right now.)
Maple... World? Was there a region like that?
(You ask to know more about this place.)
If you want details on this place, you should see our leader. But never mention that you are helping Humanitas because <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> won't like it.
We have our reasons. Anyways, I warned you to be careful. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> is inside.

Let me give you a tip. If <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> is uncooperative, she'll relax a little if you bring resources for us. Let's see. <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001348$</font> you get by defeating <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:25022202$</font> will be enough.
<font color="#909090">(I need to meet their leader for now.)</font>
Where is <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font>? She's in here. Go inside.
Haven't seen you before. Who are you?
(Say that you are from <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font> and came here to explore as a request by Humanitas.)
I want details of this pla—
A pawn of Humanitas! <font size='40'>Get out this instant!</font>
How shameless of them to ask help from the refugees they abandoned. It's useless even if you put on a bewildered expression!

The refugees expelled by Tairen stayed in this area and moved to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020030$</font>, where Humanitas is, by avoiding Kharon. You won't say that you don't know when you kept on accepting refugees, right?
But you didn't do anything when we were suffering and couldn't move anywhere because of those black capes! You didn't attempt to rescue us or help by sending resources. You didn't do anything at all.
You said Humanitas was for everyone. But you cut away those you didn't need in the end, right? Like father, like daughter.
(Say that Humanitas was fighting alone on two fronts, Tairen and the Daemon Army, due to the sudden appearance of the Daemon Army.)
And to be exact, I'm not a member of Humanitas but the Maple Allia—
Get out of my sight <font size='40'>now!</font>
<font color="#909090">(Sh-should go back for now. She has strong hostility towards Humanitas. But she might relax a little if the refugees are helped out.)</font>
Get out of my sight now!
Haha, seems like things didn't go well with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> looking at your face. Did you get the item?

Thanks. While you were gathering the item, I told <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> that you taught the Kharon a lesson. When I told him you even obtained resources for us, she seemed a little relaxed.
Go and see her as she wants to see you again.
I heard from <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004571[gender:0]$</font> that you helped us.
Let me formally introduce myself. I am <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font>, leader of the refugees. ...I'm not doing this because I want to.
I'll be direct. Did Humanitas send you to support us?
(Say that they are waiting for the investigation report beyond the foothold, and will provide immediate support if they knew the refugees needed help.)
(You added that the reason you came here is because <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font> made it a top priority to watch this place closely.)
Are you saying Humanitas didn't know of our situation because of those darn black capes? Hm... That seems plausible. Fine, I'll trust you for now.
You wanted details on this place, right? What exactly do you want to know?
(Say that you are looking for the commander of those he called black capes, and ask if anything suspicious happened in the surroundings.)
Something suspicious? Well, you should ask <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font> who knows all the rumors in this vicinity. He was here even before we settled down.

Here, take this recommendation. The house with a shiny crystal on top of a green roof is where <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font> lives. It would be great if you get the information you're looking for.

You want me to tell you again where the information dealer lives? The house with a shiny crystal on top of a green roof is where <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font> lives. You'll know right away as there's only one house.
Welcome! I, <font color="#ffd200">$npc:11004576$</font>, buy and sell all things.
But I don't do business with just anyone. Are you a trustworthy human?
A-ha, it's been a while since I saw a recommendation from <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font>. I'll listen since you are trustworthy.
Then I'll receive you as a client. Welcome to <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004576$</font>'s shop where anything is bought and sold! What do you want?
(Ask for recent suspicious rumors or anything he knows on the black capes.)
A-ha, it seems you are pursuing <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>, right?
Don't like down on me, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004576$</font>, who knows everything. Anyways, that information is quite expensive. Do you have a lot of money?
(Argue what he's talking about when you brought the recommendation.)
Ha! You don't know much of the world, do you? All this recommendation does is prove that you're trustworthy. Is anything free in this world?
(Ask whether you could work it off.)
I see you don't have money... Fine, then bring me an item I need. I'll accept an item in place of the information fee.
Defeat <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:25022602$</font> in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font> and get <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001349$</font>.

Rafflesias used to get along with us leshies, but strange rafflesias have been sighted lately that destroy everything in their path! It seems that have been corrupted by something and I would like to analyze it.
This needs to be confirmed as the base could be in danger. However, I am <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font> and can't fight. Bring it instead of me.
That information can't be sold. Well, you might find out on your own if you're lucky, but that's for later. Bring the item I need for now.
Defeat <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:25022602$</font> in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font> and get <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001349$</font>.
(You hold out the seed you obtained.)
It really looks strange! I need to look into this separately. Thank you!
Now, I'll give you the information you wanted. Listen well.
Many materials have been transported to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font> recently, and there's this constant sound as if a large machine is working. Don't you think it's suspicious?
That area is swarming with the Kharon and there are no Tairen soldiers. Why is there machine sounds?
My intuition tells me <font color="#ffd200">something</font> is being made in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>!
(Say that it needs to be checked out.)
Once you go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>, you can check out the situation by using the binoculars. Good luck!

<font color="#909090">(I should take a look around <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font> and report what I've found out so far. Let's go back to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font> after observing.)</font>
I have nothing more to tell you even if you stay here. Go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font> and check for anything suspicious by using the binoculars.
You're back, $MyPCName$. You must be tired, but could I ask for a report now?
(You told what you went through in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020066$</font> and how you met <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004574[gender:1]$</font>.)

So they couldn't come to us because of the Daemon Army! Thank you for resolving <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004574[gender:1]$</font>'s misunderstanding, $MyPCName$. I will deploy members of Humanitas right now to provide them support!
(You also relayed the fact that you met <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font> and discovered a suspicious facility in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>.)
I will go and find out what kind of facility it is!
Isn't it dangerous even for <font color="#ffd200">Strike Team $npcName:11004578[gender:0]$</font>?
There are too many uncertainties. Infiltrating the facility is akin to suicide.
There is nothing we can find out with the information we just heard. Unfortunately, we need more information...
That's a good idea, kitten. We just need to get more information if we need them! I'm also curious of that <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font>. Shall we go on a date for a change?
Stop bothering $MyPCName$! And <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004579[gender:1]$</font>, you were going to look for traces of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> with me!

I was just joking and Nainai is being so scary. Looks like I have no choice. I have to pursue <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> with Nainai. I leave the suspicious facility to you.
(Say that you'll be back in no time.)
Hm? Didn't you say you'll be getting information on the suspicious facility from <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font>? Hurry as we have no time to waste.
Oh, you're back. Wait a moment as I'm with another client.
It's you again. I'm getting tired of this.

A strange land appeared in the sky and I strongly felt <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>'s aura from that land. I was going around in order to kill him and discovered <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font>.
(Ask if the other Runeblades came as well.)
I don't need them. ...They haven't recovered and will be a hindrance. Resting during that time is helping me.
(Say that he doesn't need to worry as they will get better.)
What? Who is worrying who? Since you also met <font color="#ffd200">$npcTitle:11004576$</font>, I should speed up my pursuit. Who knew my path would overlap with a rookie like you?
Are you two done with your greetings? Finish your conversation outside. Time is money!
We don't have such a relation—
It seems you two know each other and the information you want is the same. Did you check out <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>?
(Say that you discovered a suspicious facility.)

<font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is preparing to operate <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> in that place. <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> is Tairen's newest weapon with tremendous power!

It seems <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> obtained <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020035$</font>. It will be troubled once <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> is in operation! If you want to win the battle against <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>, you must act quickly.
(Say that you appreciate it and will depart immediately.)
Since you were recommended by <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> and the seed you brought was a great help, let me give you one advice.
It's impossible to face <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> barehanded. You'll be no match.
Fight strength with strength! What do you think of stealing <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>? If you obtain the blueprint, you will know how to control <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>.
You should go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020035$</font> and obtain <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint.
(You thank for the advice and say you'll depart immediately.)
You didn't pay for the information yet. Are you running away? If you don't have money, work it off.
(Say that you will share the blueprint with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> when you obtain it.)
You must share it! I'll follow once I take care of this.
(Tell him to meet you in front of the suspicious facility in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>.)
Hurry and come here. I have a mountain of things I need.
(Hurry to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020035$</font> before you get caught in it together.)
Go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020035$</font> and obtain <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint.
<font color="#909090">(I'm here but how do I go inside the factory?)</font>
Well, I guess something will happen if I play around with the computer.
Well, I guess something will happen if I play around with the computer.
Well, I guess something will happen if I play around with the computer.
I've done hacking errands many times, this was nothing! Why don't we go inside?
Ask me for information inside the factory.
Ask where you can find <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint.
This is a robot factory managed by Tairen. Superior soldiers for the kingdom are manufactured here.
Say that you will ask something else.
<font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> is top secret. Do you have permission to access top secret information?
Confirmed. You can find <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint in the innermost part of the factory.
However, you need to shut down the security facility in order to go inside. Please enter the code to shut down the security facility.
Code? Hm... I'll just go in for now. All I need to do is quickly get the blueprint and go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020067$</font>.
You can find <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>'s blueprint in the innermost part of the factory.
You're finally here. I was tired of waiting and almost went in first.
It's a simple structure. I've already familiarized myself.
I'll return the blueprint as you need it more.
(Say that you know it like the back of your hand and don't need it.)
<font color="#909090">(I don't like him, but his skills will be a great help. I should ask him to go together.)</font>

(You say that Sky Fortress is working with Humanitas, a local group, to apprehend <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>, and whether <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> would like to join after they get <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>.)
There's no need for me to be with rookies. I refuse.
(Retort that he doesn't know this place and tell him to stop being stubborn.)
...I'll go together this time, but there's no next time.
(Say he made the right choice and you will radio him.)
Let's see, so I match the code and... done. Hello, can everyone hear me?
Loud and clear. Did you find out anything on the suspicious facility?
(Say that the facility was made by <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> to operate Tairen's newest weapon, <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>.)
<font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>?! It looks like <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> finally completed it.
(Say that you happened to meet <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> and will return together after weakening <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>.)
(Say he's a comrade... who accompanied you before.)

He must be trustworthy if he's your friend, $MyPCName$. Very well, I'll hear the details after you weaken <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>. Return safely as we have something to relay from our end as well.
Why are you here? Didn't you say you're going to weaken <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>?
You returned safely. Did you succeed in weakening <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>?
(Say that you succeeded in stealing <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font> from <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>.)
This is the best as we also have loot. Now, why don't you introduce your comrade?
(Say he's <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font>, a Runeblade of Terrun Calibre.)
It's my first time seeing someone from Terrun Calibre. Nice to meet you. I'm <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004577[gender:1]$</font>, captain of Sky Fortress.
I heard there was someone defeating the Daemon Army and Tairen soldiers lately. So, it was you! Nice to meet you. I am <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font>, leader of Humanitas.
Since we're done with introductions, it's time you heard what we found out.
$MyPCName$, while you were weakening <font color="#ffd200">Arkeon</font>, we focused on following <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>'s tracks.

We did a comparative analysis of the data on <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> that we collected in <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font> with the data in this region possessed by Humanitas and found that <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is commanding the Daemon Army from <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font> which is beyond <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font>.
Ah, do you need a detailed explanation? You have this look as if you don't understand.
(You try to refuse saying you're fine.)

Back to the topic. We were preparing to rush in after finding out <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>'s location, but <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004580[gender:1]$</font> reported that an unidentified energy source was detected at the gateway towards <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font>. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004580[gender:1]$</font>?
Yes, we don't know what it is exactly, but a very strong energy source has been detected. Humanitas also requested analysis of that energy source but...
It's a mixture of the energy of Tairen and the Daemon Army. Even we have failed in analyzing that energy source. There is too much risk to charge in like this.
(Say that you will confirm it with your eyes.)

(Say that you are against <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> coming because he's the only one who can stop <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> if something happens to you.)

(Above all, since <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> doesn't know Kritias that well yet, it's best to get an explanation of this place from <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font>.)
Then it's decided. Oh, $MyPCName$. While you're going there, could you decrease the number of the Daemon Army in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font>? I want to send a scout there.
As you go to check the unidentified energy source with your eyes, it would be great if you could also decrease the number of the Daemon Army in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font>.
You're back. Did you find out the identity of the unidentified energy source?
(You show everyone the picture you took in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020070$</font>.)
(Ask if she knows what it is.)
It looks a little different but... it's <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font>, a weapon that used to guard Tairen.
<font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> was a weapon that used to guard Tairen in the past. It was superior weapon that was right in front of the kingdom.

However, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> discarded it after successfully developing a new-type weapon. I haven't seen it for a while and thought it was scrapped, but it looks like that wasn't the case.

I think the animosity towards <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> for being discarded made <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> to cooperate with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>.

But how can <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> go against Jessica and cooperate with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>? Aren't all robots made by Tairen under <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>'s control?

Not all follow <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> completely. In the case of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font>, it had a 'learning' feature to upgrade on its own as it was the gatekeeper of Tairen. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> became <font color="#ffd200">sentient</font> through repeated learning.

Afterwards, it occasionally ignored <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>'s orders. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> wasn't pleased with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> and focused on developing a new-type weapon which she succeeded. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> received the command to shut down as soon as the new-type weapon test ended.

Afterwards, it occasionally ignored <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>'s orders. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> wasn't pleased with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> and focused on developing a new-type weapon which she succeeded. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> received the command to shut down as soon as the new-type weapon test ended.
I didn't think it would obediently shut down, but I never imagined it would flee and work with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>... The situation isn't good.

Since <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> is cooperating with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>, it must have learned a new ability due to its superior performance. Who knew it would be guarding the way to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font>? Retreat... that is something we might need to consider.
Never! I will definitely get rid of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>. I will cut down anything that is in the way.
(You agree and won't back out after making it this far.)

I understand how you feel, but it's too dangerous! As long as <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:23504001$</font> is guarding <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font>, there is no way for us to get near!
(Say that you will stop <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> and the rest will take that chance to enter <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font>.)
(You look at both <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004584[gender:0]$</font> and <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004577[gender:1]$</font>, and say you trust them.)
I understand how you feel, but it's too dangerous!
I trust in my member. All hands, prepare for entry!
Sigh... Fine. Since everyone is determined, I will place my trust as well.
But I'm still against $MyPCName$ going alone. You need to be prepared to face <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font>.

<font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> always has a barrier to protect itself. You will just be wasting time and stamina if you go against <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> without any preparations.
But even <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> can't keep up its barrier in front of royalty. It's because being armed next to royalty is treason.
Go with me, $MyPCName$. If we go together, it will be possible to take down <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font>.
Everyone is giving their all, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004583[gender:0]$</font>. I must do what I can as well. There won't be problems because even I received combat training.

<font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font>, you are the leader of Humanitas! You need to think of your position! How could you not know that Humanitas would fall if something happens to you?

Thank you for understanding, $MyPCName$. Since <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004582[gender:1]$</font> can't go with you, let's make a device to trick <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font>.

It's an aetherine disruptor that makes it look like the same aetherine in me is flowing in you, $MyPCName$. If you have that device, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> will recognize you as royalty.
But we need many <font color="#ffd200">$itemPlural:30001350$</font> to make the device... I don't know if we can obtain them here.

<font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font> is made only in Tairen. Only the instituiton under direct control of the royal family has the decomposition technology to make even the tiniest power to contain aetherine.
Ah, refugees who were recently expelled from Tairen might have them. Since they don't have much use for them, why don't we help the refugees for <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font>?
That's a great idea! $MyPCName$, could you go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020066$</font> and ask their leader, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font>?
$MyPCName$, could you go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020066$</font> and ask their leader, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font>?
It's you. What do you want?
<font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font>? We might not have it since that's a luxury item even among aetherine. Where are you going to use it?
But how does an outsider know of <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font>?
(You need the aetherine disruptor to trick the gatekeeper you must defeat in order to kill the leader of the black capes.)
We would like to provide our support in driving out the black capes, but we are in this situation. We don't have the material and wouldn't be able to give you even if we did have it.
<font color="#909090">(Tch, is there no way to obtain it?)</font>
But don't give up. I'll give you information since Humanitas promised to support us in the future.

Those blasted Tairen observing us have poor skills, but have a high social position. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004573[gender:1]$</font> said she often hears them boasting of their wealth and power.

We scolded her to not do anything dangerous and act like a child, but we should make good use of this information, right? They should have <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font>. Take to your heart's content.
We're the ones who are thankful that you're getting rid of them. Try to get as many as possible.
Those blasted Tairen in the vicinity should have <font color="#ffd200">$item:30001350$</font>. Take to your heart's content.
You're back, $MyPCName$! Did you get the material?
(The refugees didn't have it, but you stole it from the Tairen soldiers after <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004574[gender:1]$</font> informed you of it.)
From the Tairen soldiers? You did very well!
We just need to assemble it. Please wait.
It's done. You can face <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004684$</font> with this. Be careful, $MyPCName$.
(Say that you'll go and meet everyone in front of <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font>.)
Good luck. Let's move out as well.
I believed you would return safely. Thanks to you, all of us entered <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020071$</font> safely.
It doesn't look like you have any big injuries. It was a wonderful operation.
A sudden energy signal has been detected! What is it?
(Say that you don't understand what they're saying.)
Right? I'm not the only one who doesn't understand. Do you understand?
It's been a while since I heard that word. Utopia is the reason <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> exists.
'Make <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font> into a utopia where everyone lives in abundance and happiness.' That was the command entered in <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>.
The word utopia and this familiar aura from that being. This is strange.
We should focus on what's important the chaotic the situation.

That is to apprehend <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>. It's dangerous to waver when the enemy is right before you. We will strike <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> as that is our initial objective.
Then are we all charging in?

No, it isn't wise for everyone to go in at once. $MyPCName$, who is most associated with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>, will go in from the front. The rest will strike <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> from the back.
If there's anything better, suggest it now.

Ah, the newly developed weapons from <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020030$</font> are being sent here right now. They are moving as fast as they can, but it will take time due to the fierce interference of the Daemon Army and Kharon.
There's no need to rush since we have come this far. Why don't we wait until we are perfectly prepared?
I agree. Let's wait until supplies arrive.
(Tell them to let you know when everything is ready.)
We have some time, but don't let your guard down. Continue to train your body as you wait.
We will definitely defeat <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> this time.
You've waited a long time, $MyPCName$. All preparations are finally done. You didn't slack off on training, did you?
Excellent. Do you remember the strategy?
Yes, we confirmed all supplies have been properly distributed. I'm a bit nervous since we have a large battle before us.
(Tell her not to worry too much as everything will work out.)
Hehe, I'm at ease a little because of your words, $MyPCName$. Shall we go now?
You are mistaken if you think you can control me now. I am... different from you.
I have no intention of living with filthy humans. I will rule over both <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font> and <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
I will stand on top of everything.
Good, everyone move out. Today is the day we end our ill-fated relationship with <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>!
Are you afraid now that we're departing? But you can't avoid it forever. Let's go and defeat <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>.
A robot? Really? <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is a robot, right?
So the one that has been giving us trouble all this time was a robot?

No, it can't be <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> because she was sealed with us. But why does <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> look exactly like <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>?
As expected of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004596[gender:0]$</font> to apply the concept of twins to AI and robots.
Did <font color="#ffd200">Arazaad</font> try to hand Terrun Calibre over to that robot? Did I hurt my fellow runeblades and became alone to get rid of a robot? This is ridiculous.

This might be confusing to all of you, but it's dangerous to remain here any longer. We don't know when <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>'s soldiers will come again. Let's move to a safe location for now.
That would be good. Let us go to <font color="#ffd200">$map:52100204$</font> in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020036$</font>.
It's been a while. How have all of you been?
(Ask where and what she has been doing.)
There was something I had to take care of alone. Don't get mad. I also had a hard time.
We were surprised at your sudden appearance. Could you explain what happened?
Ah, I guess that was wrong since you were also sealed with me. I take that back.
I'm not here to play with you. I may have failed last time, but not this time. It won't end with a simple seal.
Oh my! I'm so scared. But you don't even know where I am. Even though you destroy the "me" here, "I" won't disappear.
I'm going to destroy this place today. And if you appear again, I will destroy that place was well.
I've heard your resolve, but my plan to turn <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font> into a utopia is already complete. You can't stop anything.
Well, it's going to be impossible, but I ran a simulation that my plan will succeed even though you destroy me. It's because my clone has inherited my will.
Clone? What are you playing at?
Ah, didn't you already meet my clone? I was expecting to receive you as a gift, but I guess it was incompetent since it's merely a clone. What a shame.

The demon in the black hood that you met is my clone. When you tried to seal me, did you think I would do nothing? I already knew you were coming and sent a part of me to <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font>.
It was to make my clone return everything to normal after I was sealed. But you arrived faster than expected and I wasn't able to completely sync my ego.

I was surprised that the clone's ego became that strong, but it can't go against me, the original. You can tell that just by looking how it subconsciously broke the seal on <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>. Do you now understand, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004603[gender:1]$</font>?
Thank you for all that nonsense. I'll destroy you right now.
Your friends are busy fighting the clone. Is it okay to waste your strength here? I sent a small gift to help my clone.
My army has already mobilized. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004603[gender:1]$</font>, I think you should hurry along.
You! The next time we meet, I will definitely destroy you.
Please do your best, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004603[gender:1]$</font>. I look forward to meeting you again.
...And that's what happened. I ran to where you were as soon as I heard that, and fortunately made it in time.
It's just one shocking thing after another. A clone...
So, you're saying <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is a clone made by <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> to break the seal, right?

She failed to completely transfer her ego because the seal was done quickly, but the initial command was already entered into <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font>. That made <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> create the blackshard and break the seal on <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
Then why did it join <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004613[gender:0]$'s Seven Commanders</font> or whatever it is? It could have went straight and break the seal.
It needed power to break the seal. It's unforgivable that Terrun Calibre and my fellow runeblades suffered because of one crazy <font color="#ffd200">AI</font>.
It's fortunate that I wasn't late.
For now... let's sort this out. <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> is dead, I mean destroyed, but we still have the Daemon Army remnants.
That's correct. We should focus on what must be done now.
Humanitas will focus on getting rid of the Daemon Army remnants. We can't miss this chance to reduce the two fronts back into one again.
(Say that you will help as well.)
Thank you. The leader of the enemy is gone, but the enemy isn't.
$MyPCName$ and Captain <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004604[gender:1]$</font>. I truly thank you for the help in driving out the Daemon Army from this land.
I have prepared a small gift since you helped us all this time.
I have prepared a small gift since you helped us all this time.
This is an official letter thanking the Maple Alliance for supporting Humanitas. It's also a letter promising to maintain an amicable relationship between Humanitas and the Maple Alliance.
It seems this letter isn't for us. You want this delivered to Empress <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004390[gender:1]$</font>, correct?
Yes, I haven't met her in person yet, but I believe she can be trusted since she sent the two of you here. Please tell her we would like to build a good relationship.
I will deliver your message, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004609[gender:1]$</font>. I was thinking of reporting to the Empress of what happened so far seeing how things have stabilized here.
$MyPCName$, is it okay if I leave this task to you?
(Say that you'll go since you're starting to miss <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font>.)

Thanks. If you're going to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02000001$</font>, use the '<font color="#ffd200">Lumiwind</font>' in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020041$</font>. You'll be able to return quickly.
If you're going to <font color="#ffd200">$map:02000001$</font>, use the '<font color="#ffd200">Lumiwind</font>' in <font color="#ffd200">$map:02020041$</font>. You'll be able to return quickly.
It seems many things happened. I can't believe that <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004430[gender:0]$</font> was a robot made by an AI in <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
Good work going through all that, $MyPCName$. It's good to see you back safe.
I feel heavy since all of you went through a lot in Kritias.
(But say that you obtained many things.)
Yes, did you say <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004603[gender:1]$</font> was the daugther of <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004431[gender:0]$</font>? I really want to see her.
(Say that <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004603[gender:1]$</font> would also want to meet the Empress who is her father's peer.)

I hope so too. Of course, I'm also curious of the leader of Humanitas, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004609[gender:1]$</font>. She will be an important figure in the relation between <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font> and <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font>.
It's all thanks to you and the members of Sky Fortress that we are able to form an amicable relationship. I am very proud of everyone.
I am very proud of you.
I want to meet them this instant, but that is after everything is taken care of.
As long as the AI called <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font> has her eye on <font color="#ffd200">Maple World</font>, we can't avoid fights.
(Say that you will need to enter the depths of <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font> to stop <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004575[gender:1]$</font>.)
I agree. $MyPCName$, please relay this to the members of Sky Fortress.
I hereby give the order to charge into the depths of <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
I hereby give the order to charge into the depths of <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
I hereby give the order to charge into the depths of <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
<font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11000057[gender:1]$</font>, report on what happened in <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font>.
That <font color="#ffd200">mechanical toy</font> is finally dead. It's a pity that we lost a valuable chess piece.
The appearance of <font color="#ffd200">Kritias</font> is to stop the destruction from light. There is nothing to be inconvenienced about as everything is proceeding as planned.
But we found the whereabouts of the <font color="#ffd200">Blue Lapenta</font>. Isn't that a great gain?
It is. What I want will be brought to me soon by another chess piece. All we need to do is wait.
Yes. Everything is according to your will, <font color="#ffd200">$npcName:11004613[gender:0]$</font>.
